BULAWAYO &ndash; Recently, multi-talented artiste Madlela Skhobokhobo hogged the limelight in the City of Kings when he garnered four nominations &mdash; the highest number by an individual artiste in the inaugural Bulawayo Arts Awards set to be held at the Large City Hall on June 30. The Daily News on Sunday&rsquo;s Jeffrey Muvundusi recently spoke to Madlela Sikhobokhobo, who was born Mothusi Bashimane Ndlovu, on his four-nomination haul and his career in general.